CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 23, 1957, pg. A14 reads: "Hill City Captains - The tea (team) captains of Hill City had a dinner meeting at the home of the chairman, Eunice W. Cook. On hand were Mmes. Elizabeth Reed, Julia Harper, John A. Cundiff, James Handley, Mrs. Marian Handley, Mrs. Wills, Mrs. Terry, Mrs. Anderson, Mrs. Delores Brown, Mrs. Gladys Brown, Mrs. Lavenia McKinney, Mrs. Bette Davis, Miss Priscilla Ward, G. Harold Griffin, Mrs. Clara Crumbley, Mrs. Adams and the hostess.  The first benefit tea will be held at Ammon Recreation Center, Sunday, April 28.  Funds will be used to renovate Hill City building. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Hill City team captains, including Eunice W. Cook, Elizabeth Reed, Julia Harper, John A. Cundiff, James Handley, Marian Handley, Mrs. Wills, Mrs. Terry, Mrs. Anderson, Delores Brown, Gladys Brown, Lavenia McKinney, Bette Davis, Priscilla Ward, G. Harold Griffin, Clara Crumbley, and Mrs. Adams, gathered for meeting in home of Eunice Cook
